Former West German Chancellor Willy Brandt, who emotionally challenged the building of the wall as mayor of West Berlin in the early 1960s, was in the front row of an invited audience. Hundreds of excited Berliners leaned from balconies and windows today to cheer Charlie's exit, snapping pictures and clapping in rhythm with the band as the crane pried the hut from its moorings and swung it away. Foreign ministers Hans-Dietrich Genscher of West Germany and Markus Meckel of East Germany also attended the ceremony. At long last, we are bringing Charlie in from the cold, he added. 